When washed the wells, the enzymatic reaction was proceeded as the list below: o-PD solution (120 μL, containing 5 mM o-PD and 5 mM H2O2 in 0.01 mM sodium acetate buffer (NaAC buffer), pH 5.5) were transferred into each well. After incubation for 50 min at RT, 20 μL of 1.0 mg·mL-1B/N-CDs diluted in NaAC buffer was mixed with the substrate solution. The fluorescence signals were recorded at 426 nm (f426
                        ) and 549 nm (f549
                        ) under 360 nm excitation, and the ratio of f549/f426
                         was calculated. The absorption signals at 431 nm were recorded. Each data point was presented as mean ± standard deviation (SD).

The repetitive experiments of the proposed immunoassay for Ara h 3 measurement had been carried out and the results are displayed in Fig. S6. Under the same conditions, it can be seen that the (f549
                        /f426
                        ) and (U431
                        ) of the five parallel determination samples were both close. The RSDs were all below 2 %, indicating that the proposed method has a good repeatability. The use of nanobody in this work improved the reproducibility of immunoassay.

Selectivity is an essential factor for appraising the behavior of the proposed ELISA. The selectivity of P43 has been verified in our previous work. As a probe, P43 has the high affinity to the target through which showed distinctive bands in Western blotting (Hu et al., 2023). Therefore, we could use P43 to estimate the dual-mode immunoassay. Some latent interfering substance in food samples including β-lactoglobulin, were investigated for detecting Ara h 3. As shown in Fig. 5
                        , only Ara h 3 produced a significant increase in fluorescence intensity ratio (f549
                        /f426
                        ) and UV absorption (U431
                        ) in relation to other interferences. The high specificity was due to the highly recognition ability of P43. From the results, they all revealed that remarkable selectivity and precise of the proposed ELISA for Ara h 3 detection even the interfering substances at high concentrations.
